        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Nonlinear isotropic elastic-plastic constitutive model (bilinear kinematic hardening) for Ti-6Al-4V ELI; contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian penalty; geometric nonlinearity (large-deformation) enabled. Model form justified by literature precedent for metallic implant FEA and confirmed adequate by validation comparison E/uval < 1.96 across all three QoIs."
      },
      "rationale": "The bilinear kinematic hardening plasticity model for Ti-6Al-4V ELI is well-established for quasi-static metallic implant simulations. Geometric nonlinearity is enabled to capture screw bending beyond the elastic regime. Frictional contact (μ=0.2, per ASTM F1717 lubrication conditions) is included at all screw-block interfaces. Model form adequacy is corroborated by the validation comparison results (all E/uval < 1.96). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
