        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "ASTM F1717 mandates a single standardized test configuration (5-degree rod angulation, 35 mm rod offset). Only this single condition was tested; multi-angle or multi-offset parametric sweep was not performed. Achieved Gradation 2 (single well-characterized test condition) against a required Gradation 3."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under the single ASTM F1717 standardized configuration (5-degree angulation, 35 mm rod offset). While this condition is highly relevant to the COU, only one test condition was exercised, limiting the ability to characterize model fidelity across the operating envelope. This yields Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3. The shortfall is offset by the high inter-laboratory reproducibility (CV < 3% across both labs) and the conservative acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference) that provide adequate confidence for the Medium-risk COU decision."
